<<.from-version "5.3.7">> By default tags are alphabetically sorted using a filter shown in the code below. There is a subfilter which uses the new configuration variable: $:/config/Tags/CustomSort/subfilter:

```
filter="[all[current]tags[]] :sort:alphanumeric:caseinsensitive[subfilter{$:/config/Tags/CustomSort/subfilter}]"
```

''Current configuration''

* The active sort subfilter is: <code><$text text={{{ [{$:/config/Tags/CustomSort/subfilter}!is[blank]else[n/a]] }}}/></code>
* The default value is: `[{!!title}]`

''Special Usecase''

If the configuration tiddler: $:/config/Tags/CustomSort/subfilter is set to an ''empty value'':

* The tags are sorted in creation order
* The tag-editor will activate drag and drop sorting

''Possible values for $:/config/Tags/CustomSort/subfilter'', //which should be chnaged by experienced users only//.

If the custom sort order is changed the subfilter in $:/config/Tags/CustomSort/subfilter will be used as the default filter to define the sort order in the view- and edit-template. 

<<.tip """The custom sort order is implemented with a [[Sort Filter Run Prefix]]. Please ''carefully'' read the documentation. This configuration is only needed if you want to overwrite the default sort order, or activate drag and drop sorting in the tag editor""">>

* `[{!!title}]`
* `[length[]]`
* `[get[color]else[zzzz]]`


